            <div type="apparatus">
                <listApp>
                    <app>
                        <note xml:id="Job-004-fn1" type="footnote">JSul.I.04: The Karaim equivalent
                            of the standard Hebrew Job 4:1 is not included in the text, probably
                            intentionally, see Job 3:1, 6:1, etc. for similar cases. The text is
                            reconstructed here on the basis of Job 2:11, and the text in ms.
                            ADub.III.84. The Hebrew text is not omitted, see BHeb. <foreign
                                xml:lang="he" style="unicode-bidi: embed;">וַיַּעַן אֱלִיפַז
                                הַתֵּימָנִי וַיֹּאמַר </foreign>
                            ‘Then Eliphaz the Temanite answered and said’ (Job 4:1). | C: <emph>Da
                                ǯoɣap berdi Elifaz ol Temanly da ajtty</emph>. | QB: <emph>Da ǯoɣap
                                berdi Elifaz ol Temanly da ajtty</emph>. | ADub.III.84: <emph>Da
                                qaruv berdi Elifaz ol Temanly da ajtty</emph>. | Kobeckaitė (2019):
                                <emph>Da qaruv berdi Elifaz ol Temanly da ajtty</emph>.</note>
                        <note xml:id="Job-004-fn2" type="footnote">An alternative translation to
                                <emph>da jyrtuv üčün tišleri jigit arslanlarnyn azasadylar</emph>,
                            introduced by the Hebrew phrase <foreign xml:lang="he"
                                style="unicode-bidi: embed;">או תאמר תרגום שני </foreign>
                            ‘or you will say a second translation’, the equivalent of BHeb. <foreign
                                xml:lang="he" style="unicode-bidi: embed;">וְשִׁנֵּי כְפִירִים
                                נִתָּעוּ </foreign>
                            ‘and the teeth of the young lions are broken’. | C: <emph>da tišleri
                                jigit aslanlarnyŋ azašyrlar</emph>. | QB: <emph>da tišleri jigit
                                aslanlarnyŋ ajrylyrlar</emph>. | ADub.III.84: <emph>da jyrtuvu üčün
                                tišlerinin jigit arslanlar azasadylar</emph>. | Kobeckaitė (2019):
                                <emph>da tišĺari kijikĺarnin uvaldylar</emph>.</note>
                        <note xml:id="Job-004-fn3" type="footnote">Hypercorrect form of
                                <emph>kečenin</emph>.</note>
                        <note xml:id="Job-004-fn4" type="footnote">Spelled <foreign xml:lang="he"
                                style="unicode-bidi: embed;">קַרְשִישִינָא</foreign>
                            .</note>
                        <note xml:id="Job-004-fn5" type="footnote">An alternative translation to
                                <emph>jančar alarny ölim burun güjeden</emph>, introduced by the
                            Hebrew phrase <foreign xml:lang="he" style="unicode-bidi: embed;">או
                                תאמר תרגום שני </foreign>
                            ‘or you will say a second translation’, the equivalent of BHeb. <foreign
                                xml:lang="he" style="unicode-bidi: embed;">יְדַכְּאוּם לִפְנֵי־עָשׁ </foreign>
                            ‘are crushed before a moth’. | C: <emph>jenčär alarny küčlü ḥastalyq
                                aldyna qujašnyŋ</emph>. | QB: <emph>jenčär alarny küčlü ḥastalyq
                                aldyna qujašnyŋ</emph>. | ADub.III.84: <emph>jančady alarny ölim
                                gijeden burun</emph>. | Kobeckaitė (2019): <emph>jančadyr alarny
                                tejzŕak komuzdan</emph>.</note>
                    </app>
                </listApp>
            </div>
